  "signature": "ed25519:7b3e1a9c2d5f8b4e0a6c3d7f1e2b9a4c5d8f0e3b6a2c9d4f7e1b5a8c3d6f0e2",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver (ANSYS Fluent 2021R2) with documented release notes and regression test suite; internal SQA checklist completed and archived. Gradation 2 requires documented version control and basic regression testing.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver is a commercially released code subject to vendor SQA processes. Version control records, release notes, and the internal simulation checklist were reviewed and found compliant with Gradation 2 requirements for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Verification against at least one analytical or manufactured solution for the governing equations used in the hemolysis simulation; documented order-of-accuracy confirmation at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy testing was performed using a manufactured solution for the incompressible Navier-Stokes equations on a simplified channel geometry. Second-order spatial convergence was confirmed for both velocity and pressure fields, satisfying Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) computed on three systematically refined meshes; GCI < 5% on the hemolysis index QoI at the nominal operating point. Gradation 2 threshold is formal GCI calculation; Gradation 3 additionally requires extrapolated solution and uncertainty quantification.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh refinement levels (4.2 M, 11.8 M, and 31.4 M cells) were evaluated. GCI on the relative hemolysis index was 2.3%, below the 5% threshold. Richardson extrapolation was applied and the fine-mesh discretization error is estimated at 1.1%, exceeding Gradation 2 and satisfying Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, outlet pressure, fluid temperature, blood analog viscosity) documented with calibrated instrumentation and traceable uncertainty estimates. Gradation 2 requires documented test conditions with stated uncertainties.",
      "rationale": "All bench-top hemolysis experiments were conducted with calibrated flow meters (±1.5% FS) and pressure transducers (±0.5% FS). Fluid temperature was maintained at 37 ± 0.5 °C. Test conditions are fully documented in the experimental protocol archived with the submission."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "The primary quantity of interest, the relative hemolysis index (RH), was compared between CFD predictions and experimental measurements across all five flow-speed operating points. The mean absolute error in RH was 8.4%, within the validation tolerance established for Gradation 2 at MRL 2. The comparison metric and tolerance band were defined prior to simulation execution in the V&V plan. Gradation 2 requires a quantitative comparison metric against experimental data, which has been performed here using the normalized RH error."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation (RH index, wall shear stress distribution) must directly correspond to the decision-relevant outputs (worst-case hemolysis operating point identification). Gradation 2 requires demonstrated correspondence between validation QoIs and COU decision outputs.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index computed in validation experiments and CFD predictions is the same metric used in the regulatory submission comparison against the predicate device. Wall shear stress fields inform the hemolysis power-law model inputs. There is a direct, documented correspondence between validation QoIs and COU decision outputs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, blood analog fluid, and operating envelope as the COU. Gradation 2 requires that validation activities cover the intended operating range with documented similarity arguments.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments were performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry, the same geometry evaluated in the COU. The blood analog fluid (glycerol-water, matched viscosity) and the five COU operating points were used in validation. A similarity argument is documented in the V&V plan."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual convergence to at least 1e-5 for all transport equations; mass imbalance below 0.01%. Gradation 1 requires documented convergence monitoring.",
      "rationale": "All simulations were run to residual convergence below 1e-6 for continuity and momentum equations. Mass imbalance across the pump domain was less than 0.005% in all cases. Convergence histories are archived in the simulation record."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, Gradation 1 for use error is acceptable; no formal independent review of simulation setup is required beyond internal checklist completion.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2 with medium model influence, Gradation 1 for use error is acceptable. An internal simulation setup checklist was completed by the lead analyst. No independent peer review of solver settings was required at this risk level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The turbulence model (SST k-ω) and hemolysis power-law constitutive model must be justified by literature precedent for rotating blood-contacting devices. Gradation 2 requires documented model-form selection rationale with supporting references.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model was selected based on established literature for rotating blood pump simulations. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model was applied consistently with prior FDA pump studies. Model-form selection is documented with five supporting references in the V&V plan."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Fluid properties (density 1056 kg/m³, dynamic viscosity 3.5 mPa·s at 37 °C), pump geometry dimensions, and rotational speed were sourced from the FDA benchmark dataset and manufacturer drawings. Sensitivity of RH to ±5% variation in viscosity was evaluated and found to produce less than 3% change in RH, confirming robustness of the input specification at Gradation 2. The required level of 2 reflects MRL 2 expectations for documented input sourcing with basic sensitivity evidence."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, Gradation 1 for test samples is acceptable; a single representative pump specimen used in validation is sufficient without statistical sampling across multiple manufactured units.",
      "rationale": "A single FDA generic centrifugal pump specimen was used for all validation experiments. At MRL 2, Gradation 1 is acceptable; multi-unit statistical sampling is not required. The pump specimen was inspected dimensionally prior to testing and found within specification."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At MRL 2, Gradation 1 is acceptable; documented correspondence between experimental and simulation boundary conditions is sufficient without formal uncertainty propagation through input parameter differences.",
      "rationale": "Simulation boundary conditions were set to match experimental measurements directly. Inlet flow rates and outlet pressures used in CFD were taken from calibrated experimental readings. At Gradation 1, formal uncertainty propagation is not required; the direct correspondence is documented in the simulation log."
    }
